**STORYLINE:** 

	You are about to be shipped to the middle east as a
	soldier,but first, you must overcome this test in cold
	environments. The desert in the middle east gets cold
	at night, and you have to learn to survive it's harsh
	weather.You and many others are set up to try to defend
	the terrorists sabotaging anything in their way to
	achieve mass destruction.
**FEATURES:**

	- Underground bombsite/base
	- Breakable Ice covering water
	- Snow particle effects
	- Easy combat
	- Different ways to attack (Confrontation, and Sniping)

Cheers,

-----=======By  J4CK8=======-----

This is Wetwork, famous from COD4, and recreated for Counter Strike: Source.

This is my first attempt at a CS:S map and a recreation of an exsisting map. For now, it is only available as a bomb/defuse map, but I shall try in future releases to improve the quality of the map and also the gameplay of the map.

Fixes/updates
	-->Rain sound should now continue to play throughout the game.
	-->Whole map has been retextured from Nodraw, which should increase FPS.
	-->Improved lighting.

Known Bugs
	-->Map has only been compiled in Fast VVIS becuase it's only a beta released at the moment and I can't leave 	   it compiling for thousands of hours.
	-->The .nav file isn't custom, so bots sometimes will camp in one spot and sometimes a terrorist will tend to 	   use a fence as a bouncy castle.

If you spot any other bugs/improvements, please comment and/or message me on Steam ( J4CK8 )

Still have not compiled the map with vvis on normal, so please, if you can, help!

.BSP and .NAV file to go into your CounterStrikeSource/Cstrike/maps folder.

email: detamic@wanadoo.fr


This is a counter strike source map. You can play up to 32 players. 

Instructions:
Extract the de_western_story.bsp and .nav files into the maps folder in the game dir.

Description:
The scene take place during west conquest, in a little town of far west. Terrorists have escaped from jail and want to take their revenge. So they want to attack Bank (A bomb site) or Mayor house (B bomb site), whereas counters have been employed to guard it...
Terrorist can use train, which can be started by pressing button of engine. 
TIPS: B site can be easily reach by train... 

Have fun!

Author: Titan1x77

Name: de_weir_beta

Release notes: This version is close to final in terms of gameplay, seems well balanced. The Beta will be ran for balance issues for a couple of months. Cosmetic touch ups and any balance changes will be made for the final version, along with any bug fixes.

Type: Bomb/Diffuse; 50 spawns, 12v12 is ideal for this map.

Description: Small intense map with quick routes to sites, with an outer area to take a long way around to Bombsite B (also branches off to A a few times). Bombsite A is more open but has a lower area underground to help cover it. Access to high vantage points everywhere and a few small areas with vent access too! 

Build notes: 2 weeks, first time using Hammer (so it's my first map), learned a lot while making this level, and enjoyed doing so. Concentrated on gameplay/balance more then looks, wanted to keep framerate as high as possible for an large outdoor area map.

Enjoy!

de_weedsmap

Hey All

This is my first attempt at mapping for CSS. The BSP file includes .nav and radar overviews etc.  I didnt have a good name for my map lol so just decided to go with my name+map. 

For up to 46 players (can add more if required on request)
The map has 2 bomb sites...the bunker and the bank which I've tried to keep equally balanced for both teams with several entrances to each site.
I tried to incorporate all the elements and aspects of good maps out there like Sniper spots, inhouse close quarter fighting, long streets, windows, hiding spots and the odd camping spots for the campers out there. 

I will be making changes to the map as im getting more used to hammer tips and tricks and will inject them into this map to get it perfect.

Please try to leave good honest feedback and advice and do not write things like THIS MAP SUCKS!! I do take critisism well and if I want to develope further as a mapper then I will read all comments and take them onboard.

Well hope you take the time to download it and enjoy.

De_weaver-secrets has many hidden surprises :)

1:  In the FIREBRIDGE ROOM, do 100 damage to the coffin in the water to make the ceiling begin to lower..
2:  At the top of WEAVER HILL, do 600 damage to the giant tombstone..  it makes a second ceiling crush those in the fire room...
3:  The third and 4th row of the graveyard have teleports..
4:  In the firebridge room, if you fall into the water, you can get back out.  
    There are invisible ramps running along both edges, with an elevator at the end of the invisi-ramp to boot ;)
5:  In the FIREBRIDGE room there is a hidden teleport, and also a teleport visa-vi the window ;)
6:  In the CT SPAWN, the entire back wall is fake.  The ceiling of the fake room may be shot out to gain entrance to tree area.
7:  In the tree area you may shoot out the floor to gain "backdoor" entrance to ct spawn (bombsite b)  (yes, same thing as 6 ;)
8:  In the water room with the SLIDING WALLS, you can shoot out the wall for a BACK ENTRANCE to T spawn, and at another area in the same room     you can even break open a hidden teleport.  
    (On all of my maps, colored steams indicate teleports.  This particular one will be pink ;)
9:  A second bomb hidden in the room with the horse?!  And guns with 420 ammo??!!!  :D
10:  Yup... there's more.  Find em!!  =D

--Weaver
